entry.title: [//media] Explicitly disable VideoFrame->WebGL 1copy upload on Android
entry.content:
PaintCanvasVideoRenderer::UploadVideoFrameToGLTexture() attempts 1-copy

upload from video frames to GL textures in one of two ways:



- Via a legacy mailbox if the source VideoFrame is not MultiplanarSI.

This codepath fails with OOP-C, but succeeds without OOP-C with

both the validating and passthrough command decoders.

- Via the command decoder's CopySharedImageToTexture() method if the

source VideoFrame is MultiplanarSI. This codepath succeeds only with

the passthrough decoder (and is entered only with the passthrough

decoder, as MultiplanarSI is gated on the passthrough decoder).



VideoFrames are not created with MultiplanarSI on Android, so it goes

into the first path. OOP-C is launched on Android, so 1-copy upload is

essentially disabled on Android. However, there are some minor corner

cases where OOP-C is disabled on Android and it might unintentionally

work.



We are looking to transition the first codepath to be via a new

command decoder API that will work with OOP-C but only with the

passthrough decoder. To decouple landing this transition with

elimination of the validating decoder on Android, this CL explicitly

disables UploadVideoFrameToGLTexture() on Android. Enabling it on

Android will be a followup effort to landing the transition.



The OneCopyUploadOfVideoFrameToGLTexture base::Feature serves as a

reverse-killswitch for this rollout: this CL disables it by default

on Android, but it can be enabled in the case of unexpected perf

problems.

callback currently receives an AutofillProfileDeepChange. This was

necessary until recently, since the deep change tracked if a change was

irrelevant for the WebDataService, since the change has just finished.

Consistent with the AutofillProfileChanged() event on the DB sequence,

the callback for the PDM is refactored to take an AutofillProfileChange.



The deep change is still necessary in the PDM, to track which changes

are currently ongoing (though will likely be refactored in a follow-up).

entry.title: PersonalDataManager(Cleaner): Remove billing address id dependence.
entry.content:
Among other tasks, the PersonalDataManagerCleaner performs disused

address deletion and profile deduplication. Both of them depend on

credit cards' billing address ids. Since the billing address is in the

process of being removed (see bug), the logic in the

PersonalDataManagerCleaner is relaxed.



In particular:

- A profile is considered disused if it hasn't been used in some time

and is not referenced as the billing address by some credit card's

billing address id. This CL removes the latter condition.

- When profile deduplication merges two similar profiles together, it

makes an effort to update the billing address ids correctly. This

logic is removed.



This removes the last relevant call to PersonalDataManager::

RemoveAutofillProfileByGUIDAndBlankCreditCardReference(), so this

function is removed as well.

entry.title: [//media] Spell out cases for using legacy mailbox to do WebGL 1c upload
entry.content:
PaintCanvasVideoRenderer::UploadVideoFrameToGLTexture() does the copy

from the VideoFrame to the GL texture either via an intermediary legacy

mailbox or by invoking the GLES2 command decoder to do the copy on the

service side via Skia. The latter is supported only in the following

cases:

* The VideoFrame is not holding a legacy mailbox (the invoked API

operates on an input SharedImage)

* The GLES2 command decoder supports YUV-RGB conversion (the validating

decoder doesn't, and it stubs out the invoked API)

* The VideoFrame is holding a multiplanar SharedImage (the invoked API

works only on a single SharedImage holding the entire source texture).



The first two of these conditions are currently implicit in the code,

which checks only the last one. The first two conditions hold because:

* if the VideoFrame is holding a multiplanar SharedImage it is not

holding a legacy mailbox

* if multiplanar SI is being used then the GLES2 command decoder must

support YUV-RGB conversion (all of multiplanar SI is dependent on

that support)



However, we will shortly be adding usage of a new GLES2 command decoder

API that works when the VideoFrame is pure software or holding a legacy

SharedImage. Thus, we will be relaxing the third condition, whereas the

first two conditions need to continue to hold. To ease this

introduction, this CL makes those conditions explicit in the code.

There is no functional change.

To test the Chrome standard library in unittests, the TestTraceProcessor must register the "chrome" stdlib module. We call the trace_processor.RegisterSqlModule() function in the TestTraceProcessor constructor to do this.

entry.title: Replace WebElements in FormTracker by (Form|Field)Ref
entry.content:
Currently autofill caches the elements it's tracking to be able to use

them when necessary. This is inconvenient because the elements are not

stored in weak pointers and this can cause memory leaks (more context

in the linked bug).



Autofill aims at resolving that by replacing the cached elements by

their renderer IDs.



This CL:

-Creates two new classes (Form|Field)Ref that hold a (form|field) as

well as its corresponding ID. This should ultimately be replaced by just

the form or field renderer ID.

-Adds a new feature kAutofillReplaceElementsByRendererIds controlling

whether we use the elements or the ids in (Form|Field)Ref.

-Replaces form and field used in FormTracker with FormRef and FieldRef.

-Refactors FormTracker::CanInferFormSubmitted.

There are three CSSValues that represent a value:

entry.title: [//gpu] Cache GpuMemoryBuffers that ScopedMapping uses
entry.content:
ScopedMapping currently creates a GpuMemoryBuffer from the passed-in

cached GpuMemoryBufferHandle, destroying the GpuMemoryBuffer when it is

destroyed. We are seeing that this behavior can cause performance

regressions when porting clients from direct usage of GpuMemoryBuffer

itself - when clients hold onto a long-lived GpuMemoryBuffer and

Map()/Unmap() from it, some GpuMemoryBuffer implementations implement

internal optimizations to limit overhead between Unmap() and subsequent

Map() operations.



This CL changes ScopedMapping to take in a GpuMemoryBuffer* rather than

a Handle. Creators of ScopedMapping now create and cache a

GpuMemoryBuffer for the relevant Mailbox rather than just the

GpuMemoryBufferHandle.



ScopedMapping still Maps()/Unmaps() the buffer at creation/destruction,

i.e., the functional behavior from the client POV is unchanged.

entry.title: [Glanceables] Add post login glanceables metrics recorder
entry.content:
Add metrics which record a histogram at each time we would want to

fetch data shown in post login glanceables. QPS can be estimated by

recording each place that data is currently fetched, and at places we

would want to trigger a fetch.



There are three places this metric is recorded at:

- Calendar event fetch

- Overview mode starting

- Full restore notification show



The metric is split by different delay amounts, being 0/15/30 seconds.

This is used to help see the effects of how queries would be throttled

when the metric is not recorded within the same 0/15/30 second interval.

entry.title: Extensions: WFH: Lacros feature parity with Ash
entry.content:
Features now (or previously) available in Lacros:

* Open a file with an extension when launch type is "single-client".

* Open files with an extension when launch type is "multiple-clients".

* Open a file in the same window instead of creating new windows.

* Permission dialog now present for user acknowledgement.

* Allowlisted extensions bypass the permission dialog.

* WFH supported QO extensions no longer use "apps".



Changes include:

* .grdp expanded to include Lacros.

* Deduplicated GetBaseNamesForIntent() for Lacros usage.

* Created new _util files to avoid duplication.

* SupportsWebFileHandlers() allowlist bypass now available for Lacros.

* Permission dialog now available in Lacros.

* Refactored unwieldy if else statement nesting in lacros controller.

* Lacros now prefers to reuse an existing window when opening a tab.

* Made some comments clearer.

* Refactored multiclient logic for clarity and possible reuse later.

* Lacros is now able to see multiple clients in the list.

* Allowlisted extensions can bypass the permission dialog.
